headline: Cisco Sales Rise as AI Hyperscalers Drive Demand
summary: Cisco  Systems logged higher revenue in its fiscal second quarter driven by increasing demand from artificial intelligence hyperscalers.  The networking company on Wednesday posted a profit of $3.18 billion, or 80 cents a share, in the quarter that ended Jan. 24, compared with $2.43 billion, or 61 cents a share, a year earlier.  Stripping out certain one-time items, adjusted per-share earnings were $1.04, ahead of the $1.02 anticipated by analysts, according to FactSet.
